rComments: cool guy. will be honest with feedback. responds to emails quickly.
Inspiring and motivating prof. I really looked forward to his lectures and always got the feeling that he cares.
Completed Jays class How to Design Almost Anything. Would highly recommend this class and had a great experience. Jay is great at helping you with your work and getting a better design.

Jay is a cool guy. Thats literally it. Too often he would bring up his own work or upcoming projects during critiques. He can also occasionally come across as condescending. I do admire his outside projects and his push for creativity, but i received little to none constructive feedback during critiques.

Jay Pooley is an animated, energetic and intelligent professor. He knows how to engage students and inspire them and expects them to inspire and impress him in return. Every studio section of the course had different internal deadlines and minor changes to expectations so knowing what was expected was sometimes a bit hazy.
Honestly an incredible lecturer and runs a great class. Would definitely love to take another studio from him.
Inspiring and caring prof. Listens to students and has a lot to share. Interesting projects.
not very informative but very fun class. is very approachable but has unrealistic expectations
Really amazing lecturer, is super approachable, helpful and gives lots of inspirational feedback. Definitely a prof that has made me think about design in an exciting way.
Great guy and good prof, but doesn't give the clearest expectations or feedback so even though I feel like he is a wealth of knowledge it doesn't necessarily get passed on.

He was a charming and nice lecturer and had run JAV101 for a while as the coordinator. So he definitely knew his stuffs and the instruction was straight-forward. However, despite that I must say I learned few things and did not receive enough feedbacks and suggestions for improvement from his class.

Jay was my first studio prof going into Architecture and I'm happy he was. He's very positive when it comes to constructive criticism, and encourages and excites his students about their work. I feel like he could use a little more connection with his students. Other than that, he's very passionate about what he does, super energetic, awesome prof!
